race.comment: SHE'S A HUSTLER (8) was a very smart winner first up as a well-backed favourite at Flemington, carrying 60.5kg there off a promising preparation last time in. She drops 6.5kg off that with the profile to say she'll continue to improve. SHE'S UNUSUAL (9) looks the danger. She's a lightly raced 6yo mare who was dominant last time at Rosehill with 53kg, scoring by three lengths. She'll take beating off that effort. JENNILALA (1) has to give the progressive ones weight but is coming through the right races, just out sprinted by a good mare in Oh Too Good off a slow speed at Caulfield last time. Up in trip now looks okay and Shinn sticks. SEA WHAT I SEE (4) looks better placed up in trip having boxed on fairly behind JENNILALA last time. She can roll forward from the wide gate and give a sight. BLINDEDBYTHELIGHT (12) is very progressive with three straight wins but this is harder and she's not well in given her ratings.
